  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Aim of this study is to investigate whether patients preoperatively treated with
      acetylsalicylic acid and/or clopidogrel have fewer perioperative bleeding and lower amounts
      of blood substitution when managed by ROTEM (whole blood coagulation analyzer) and MULTIPLATE
      (thrombocyte function analyzer).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
